# Tailwind CSS Best Practices

## Automatic Checks

The agent will verify:
- ✅ Use of design system components vs raw HTML
- ✅ CSS variables vs hardcoded colors
- ✅ Proper dark mode patterns
- ✅ Consistent spacing and typography
- ✅ `cn()` utility usage

## Design System Components vs Raw HTML

```tsx
// ❌ Incorrect - Raw HTML
<button className="bg-blue-500 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Click</button>

// ✅ Correct - Design System
import { Button } from "@axori/ui";
<Button variant="primary" size="md">Click</Button>
```

## CSS Variables vs Hardcoded Colors

```tsx
// ❌ Incorrect - Hardcoded hex color
className="bg-[#E8FF4D] text-black"

// ✅ Correct - CSS variable
className="bg-[rgb(var(--color-accent))] text-black"
```

Available CSS variables:
- `--color-primary` - Primary brand color
- `--color-accent` - Accent color (#E8FF4D)
- `--color-bg-dark` - Dark mode background
- `--color-bg-dark-card` - Dark mode card background

## Dark Mode Patterns

Use Tailwind `dark:` classes instead of conditional `isDark` logic:

```tsx
// ❌ Incorrect - Conditional logic
<div className={isDark ? "bg-[#1A1A1A]" : "bg-white"}>

// ✅ Correct - Tailwind dark: classes
<div className="bg-white dark:bg-[rgb(var(--color-bg-dark-card))]">
```

## Spacing and Typography Consistency

Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently:
- `p-2` - 8px
- `p-4` - 16px
- `p-6` - 24px
- `gap-4` - 16px
- `gap-6` - 24px

Use Typography component instead of raw HTML:
```tsx
// ❌ Incorrect
<p className="text-lg">Content</p>

// ✅ Correct
import { Typography } from "@axori/ui";
<Typography variant="body-lg">Content</Typography>
```

## cn() Utility Usage

Use `cn()` for conditional classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from "@axori/ui";

<div className={cn(
  "base-class",
  condition && "conditional-class",
  anotherCondition && "another-class"
)}>
```

